text: Love your work, <@UKLV35EEM>! I really want to play with the MFM one day...

Hey David, thanks for the link I had never head of Loyc trees, I'm using S-Expr for now but it sounds like something I should investigate. TLang for now is more like an evolving spec than runnable code, currently available here <https://bitbucket.org/sebastien/tlang/src/default/> -- I'm working on publishing the whole design docs in a more accessible format when I land in Wellington. I'm surprised they didn't take you, did you try the skilled worker visa? There's also the Edmund Hilary Fund <https://www.ehf.org/>
